---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionIntro from '../components/SectionIntro.astro';
---

<BaseLayout page="support">
  <section class="page-hero section-pad"><div class="shell"><SectionIntro eyebrow="SUPPORT" title="Help with every step." description="Create transcripts, translate speech, edit subtitles, and export captioned videos directly on your device." /></div></section>
  <section class="support-section section-pad"><div class="shell support-guide">
    <article><p class="eyebrow">CONTACT SUPPORT</p><h2>Need help from a person?</h2><p>For assistance, bug reports, purchase questions, or feature suggestions, email <a href="mailto:batchcompressvideos@gmail.com">batchcompressvideos@gmail.com</a>. Include your device model, iOS or iPadOS version, app version, language pair, video length, what happened, steps to reproduce it, and a screenshot when available. Please do not send private videos or sensitive material unless necessary and you are comfortable sharing it.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">HOW IT WORKS</p><h2>Start with a video, finish with a share-ready version.</h2><ol><li>Select a video from Photos or Files.</li><li>Choose the spoken language and create a timed transcript.</li><li>Review, edit, and translate the transcript.</li><li>Adjust subtitle appearance and placement.</li><li>Export a completed video or subtitle file.</li></ol><p>Processing is performed locally on your device. Your videos, audio, transcripts, translations, and subtitles are not uploaded to our servers.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">SELECTING A VIDEO</p><h2>Can’t find or open a video?</h2><ul><li>Confirm photo or file access permission.</li><li>Make sure an iCloud video has finished downloading and is available locally.</li><li>Try opening it in Photos first and confirm your device supports the format.</li><li>Check available device storage.</li></ul><p>On iPhone or iPad, go to Settings → Apps → Video Translate Transcriber → Photos to review access. With limited access, confirm the intended video is selected.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">TRANSCRIPTION</p><h2>Improve an inaccurate transcript.</h2><p>Background noise, music, multiple speakers, quiet or distant speech, fast speech, accents, echo, microphone quality, incorrect language selection, and specialized names can affect accuracy. Select the correct spoken language, use clear speech when possible, choose the hard-to-hear audio option for difficult audio, and review and correct important text before translating or sharing.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">TRANSLATION & SUBTITLES</p><h2>Review every important line.</h2><p>Automated translations can miss slang, humor, idioms, names, terminology, regional expressions, and context. The app is not a certified translation service. Review both the source transcript and translated subtitles before exporting, especially for legal, medical, financial, or professional use. You may edit wording, timing, size, color, background treatment, and placement; shorter subtitle lines are usually easier to read.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">PROCESSING & EXPORTS</p><h2>When processing is slow or fails.</h2><p>Processing time depends on video length and resolution, audio quality, transcription mode, translation needs, styling, device model, memory, and storage. Keep the app open, avoid demanding apps, connect power for longer videos, and try a shorter clip. If processing or export fails, confirm the video plays normally, storage is available, the original remains accessible, and the destination supports the selected format. Restart the app or device, try another supported video, and install the latest compatible app and system updates.</p></article>
    <article><p class="eyebrow">PURCHASES</p><h2>Subscriptions, lifetime access, and refunds.</h2><p>The weekly plan is currently $4.99 per week, with a three-day trial for eligible new subscribers. It renews unless canceled through Apple. Lifetime access is currently a $49.99 one-time purchase and does not renew. Apple controls final price, currency, taxes, trial eligibility, billing, and refund decisions. To restore an eligible purchase, sign in with the original Apple Account, open the purchase or settings screen, and select Restore Purchases. To cancel a weekly subscription: Settings → your name → Subscriptions → Video Translate Transcriber → Cancel Subscription.</p></article>
  </div></section>
  <section class="support-contact section-pad"><div class="shell contact-card"><p class="eyebrow">PRIVACY & LEGAL</p><h2>Your content stays local.</h2><p>Selected videos, transcripts, translations, subtitles, and exports are processed on your device and are not stored on our servers. Use of the app is subject to the Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, and Apple’s applicable App Store terms.</p><a class="button" href="mailto:batchcompressvideos@gmail.com">Email support <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
